<TITLE> Nasim hospitalised after suffering stroke </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 24 (bdnews24.com)Detained Awami League leader Md Nasim was admitted to LabAid Specialised Hospital on Tuesday, after suffering a stroke. Inspector general of prisons Brig Gen Zakir Hasan told bdnews24.com that the former minister was admitted to hospital at noon. LabAid spokesperson Mesbah Azad said the seriously ailing AL leader is being treated at the Intensive Care Unit under Prof MH Shahriar Sabet. The former home, post and telecommunications minister, and member of Awami League's executive council, was arrested on Feb 2, 2007, from his Dhanmondi residence on charges of corruption. A court has already sentenced Nasim to 13 years imprisonment for concealing wealth related information and acquiring assets beyond his known income. The trial of another graft case filed against him, involving setting up of a T&T digital telephone line, is underway. bdnews24.
